- Recipe pass
    - date: 2026-05-03
    - promoted: 3 recipes
        - workshop-critique-of-a-draft
            - chain: ask-strategic-not-interpretive → hollywood-version → cornfeld-principle → take-responsibility-for-every-element
            - scenario: workshop critique, editorial pass, or self-revision conversation that needs to convert interpretive talk into actionable revision decisions
            - intrinsic ordering: step 1 supplies the disposition (strategic re-posing) that makes the discussion actionable; step 2 supplies the destination (Hollywood version) that step 3's Cornfeld test depends on; step 3 surfaces the units worth auditing in step 4 at element scope. Each step's failure mode if skipped or done out of order is documented in the recipe.
            - worked example: omitted; Saunders walks each step in its own chapter but does not walk all four on a single draft in one passage.
        - draft-by-energy-bypass
            - chain: energy-not-aspiration → escalation-by-vocabulary-constraint → follow-the-voice → iterative-preference-revision
            - scenario: the writer-self-image trap — technically careful work coming back as "interesting" rather than alive, with the writer who would reason the trap away being the same writer who produced the slack
            - intrinsic ordering: step 1 diagnoses the trap and commits to following energy (without it the constraint exercise's surfaced voice has no criterion for keeping); step 2 bypasses the writer-self-image in a single session (without it follow-the-voice channels the same self-image); step 3 sustains the surfaced register into a draft of meaningful length (without it the writer has a fragment, not a draft); step 4 produces the highly organized terminal product (without it the chain produces an interesting draft but not a finished one).
            - worked example: omitted; Saunders walks each step in its own chapter and his post-Hemingway-mountain career arc is the implicit composition.
        - build-character-tolstoy-arc
            - chain: increasing-specification → matrix-of-facts → mind-to-mind-vantage-shifts → transformation-by-redirected-energy
            - scenario: drafting a story whose central work is rendering one character across an arc culminating in transformation
            - intrinsic ordering: step 1 supplies the particular person the rest of the prose is rendering (without it the prose has nothing to render); step 2 supplies the factual register that produces involuntary buy-in (without it the specification is squandered through editorialized assertion); step 3 supplies the vantage rotation that makes moral architecture felt (it depends on step 2's register to keep interiors fact-shaped during rotation); step 4's redirected-energy climax depends on all three priors — a particular person, a factual idiom for the climactic action, and the moral architecture the rotation produced.
            - worked example: Saunders walks all four steps on Vasili in "Master and Man" — the most integrated single-story demonstration in the book.
    - candidates considered and rejected
        - revising-a-stalled-draft (basic-drill or page-break-diagnostic → cornfeld or truncation-test → iterative-preference-revision): rejected as too disjunctive. Steps 1 and 2 each have an "or" that gives the chain four branches before it produces a unit-level test, and the choice between basic-drill and page-break-diagnostic is timing-dependent (after-finished vs mid-read) but the rest of the chain is the same on either branch. The disjunctions make it less a recipe than a family of revisions; the existing contrasts-relationship between basic-drill and page-break-diagnostic and the existing extends-relationship between truncation-test and cornfeld already capture the composability without the chain needing to be promoted.
        - rubin's-vase-thematic-charge (persistent-self-contradiction → withhold-the-resolving-interior or persistent-self-contradiction → belief-by-character-attribution → withhold-the-resolving-interior): rejected because the existing extends-relationship (withhold extends persistent) and body see-also notes ("commonly fire together"; "the macro skill setting up the configuration the moment-skill protects") capture the composability without the recipe needing to be promoted. The chain is real and its ordering intrinsic, but the atomic skills' related-sections already encode the workflow at a level a writer can act on. A recipe would restate what the extends-relationship and body notes already say. If a future user finds they want a procedural workflow for this specifically, promotion is the right call; for now, the existing cross-references suffice.
        - drafting-from-voice-or-energy-seed via is-it-helping (is-it-helping → energy-not-aspiration → follow-the-voice): rejected because is-it-helping is a meta-disposition for receiving any craft model, not a step in a drafting chain. The chain reduces to the second and third steps, which are already documented as see-also-sequential in the atomic skills. The promoted draft-by-energy-bypass recipe captures the more disciplined version of this scenario via the four-step chain that includes the constraint-bypass and revision steps.
    - .gitkeep cleanup: removed skills/saunders/recipes/.gitkeep
